  <result type="2">
   <title>
    <narrative xml:lang="EN">Consumer governments, civil society organisations and buying companies have access to data that motivates and enables them to more effectively understand, identify and mitigate deforestation risks in timber and other FRC supply chains</narrative>
   </title>
   <indicator measure="2">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Number of buyers that are strengthening existing company commodity specific policies (that protect forest landscapes) and progressing on policy implementation against agreed standards for deforestation commitments (the Accountability Framework Initiative)</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Number of upstream/downstream companies in the corporate performance database that have deforestation commitments for all commodities and report progress increased since the previous year.</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2020">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">59/228 (26%) downstream companies in Forest 500 have deforestation commitments for all commodities, 10/59 report progress on deforestation commitments for all commodities.</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-04-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2022-12-31"></period-end>
    </period>
   </indicator>
   <indicator measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Number of European Commission agencies and/or national governments that provide statements demonstrating the contributions of Global Canopy data and analyses to the development, implementation, and/or monitoring of policies to reduce overseas environmental impacts</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Number of consumer governments using Global Canopy Data</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline iso-date="2021-04-01" value="3" year="2020">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the first 6 months after the 2019 Forest 500 data was launched: the annual report was downloaded over 2,500 times, the data was downloaded 655 times, and the team engaged with 12 NGOs on the use of Forest 500 data in their work. In 2020 the Trase data was downloaded more than 750 times, the team engaged with 11 organisations and 3 consumer governments (UK, Belgium and Norway) to support their use of the data, and Trase was referenced in publications by the European Parliament and UK Parliament</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-04-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2022-12-31"></period-end>
     <target value="7"></target>
    </period>
   </indicator>
   <indicator measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Number of instances that Global Canopy data is used by target audiences, including governments, civil society organisations and/or accountability processes to monitor corporate performance and guide targeted engagement</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Number of accountability or enabling organisations using Global Canopy Data</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline value="12" year="2020">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the first 6 months after the 2019 Forest 500 data was launched: the annual report was downloaded over 2,500 times, the data was downloaded 655 times, and the team engaged with 12 NGOs on the use of Forest 500 data in their work. In 2020 the Trase data was downloaded more than 750 times, the team engaged with 11 organisations and 3 consumer governments (UK, Belgium and Norway) to support their use of the data, and Trase was referenced in publications by the European Parliament and UK Parliament</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-04-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2022-12-31"></period-end>
     <target value="40"></target>
    </period>
   </indicator>
